description: A collection of weird comics and illustrations. At least one story about an evil pig.

Traumatized by her lover's betrayal, housekeeper Louisa Grey has withdrawn from romance and dedicated herself to her job. But she is secretly and hopelessly in love with her playboy boss, Argentinian billionaire Rafael Cruz. When Rafael comes home to discover her sobbing alone in the kitchen, he grabs her wrists, pushes her against the wall and savagely kisses her. But a fortuitous fate awaits them after their explosive night of passion?
name: Vol. 1

description: EMT Rachel Brant is troubled by a mysterious onset of sleepwalking episodes. Night after night, the same man, who apparently is her lover, appears in her dream. A tragic ending always awaits them. Haunted by the visions, Rachel struggles to understand what is happening. One day, she encounters the spitting image of her dream lover. Irresistibly attracted to the dangerous man, she warns herself not to get too close-fearing the same tragic fate as her dream.
name: Vol. 1

description: Out of work and deep in debt, Alice has a PhD and no prospects, but an old hat shop is hiring for the summer, and she always did look good in hats.

volume.name: She Always Looked Good in Hats

description:
The Chippewa Vendetta

Silvertongue 30XX: Space-Time District Attorney follows the story of Silvertongue Hernandez and a rat-pack of time-travelling lawyers, specialised in revisiting (or more like crashing), so-called "Trials of the Century" throughout space-time. Silvertongue, a selfish, dark, ego-centric, womanizer and addict, will encounter the most bizarre of adventures in search of Reality 2; a parallel multi-verse he and his motley crew are carefully crafting, which will possibly mean salvation for us all. Or, will it?
name: The Chippewa Vendetta

description: Imagine your best friend is the hottest celebrity on the planet! He promised you that if he ever made it big, he'd hook you up. You move to Hollywood to take him up on his offer and realize not only are you not wanted, but you've already been replaced!

Four dissimilar high school seniors come together to compete in their school's battle of the bands. Sharing a love for playing rock and roll, the members name the band "The Stereotypical Freaks" because they feel stereotyped by their classmates - smart kid, geek, star athlete and quiet weirdo... when in fact they know they are much more than those labels that have been placed on them. When one member reveals life altering news, winning the competition takes on more of a meaning to each member. Scared and angry, upset and yet still with a lot of resolve they set out to win one for the good guys... will they?

Seven asinine adventures starring Mind's Eye and Destruct-O-Tron, the world's worst superheroes! From naked unicorn rides to arena rock concerts to lucha libre smackdowns, this remastered short story collection features the Super Haters failing in all kinds of super-powered pursuits.

Control over the multiverse is at stake.

Davis, Department A's best "viewer", is tasked to lead a team into one of their rival's artificially created dimensions. If they can find the right switch to get in, assassinate a key senator and get out, the power will swing in their favor. They've got a defector to show them where the switch is, but after that, it's up to them...

Lizard Woman and Vulturella are natural foes in the wrestling ring, but outside of it, Lizard Woman is just Lizz, a struggling single mom. Until one night when Vulturella starts going all out against Lizard Woman! Why is Vulturella trying to tire out Lizard Woman?! Wrestling action and superheroics from Jack Teagle, creator of Fight! from Nobrow Press.

Welcome to Weirdworld, a land of legend and lore! Meet Tyndall, a lost elf on a dangerous quest -- to the heart of evil and beyond! One that will unite him with the beautiful Velanna, and forge an alliance for the ages. Together with grumpy dwarf Mud-Butt, these warriors of the shadow realm will brave the City of Seven Dark Delights, face the fallen god Darklens and meet the Dragonmaster of Klarn. But will they ever find their way home?

Collects Marvel Premiere #38; material from Marvel Super Action (1976) #1, Marvel Fanfare (1982) #24-26, A Marvel Super Special #11-13, Epic Illustrated #9, 11-13.
name: TPB

description: The start of the adventures of Jolanne de Valcourt a fiery young woman, rebellious and feisty
name: Bâtarde

description: Following the trap fomented by his half-brother Philip, Jolanne finds accused of the murder of Isabelle de Marsac, the mother of her friend Laura.
name: Brigande

deck: Trapped by his brother, and sentenced for a crime she did not commit, Jolanne is shipped to India.
name: Esclave

description: Jolanne, now Jeanne Dubois, is sold to a brothel madam who intends to bring her to heel. But "Jane" did not see it that way.
name: Maîtresse

description: Number 818
name: Il bracciale perduto

description: Officialy, the slave trade had been abolished in Zanzibar, but the illegal human trafficking is still going on. Adam Wild is there to put an end to it. Many people are scheming to kill him... but scheming is easier than actually managing to kill! And making Adam angry is not a wise move!
name: Gli Schiavi di Zanzibar

volume.name: Prince Valiant in the Days of King Arthur

description: There's a new villain in Gotham called Planet King. Every crime he commits employs a different power, each one based on a different planet in the solar system.
name: The Crimes of Planet King Part 1 of 4

description: Everyone has a bad day every once in a while, but with someone as clumsy as Archie, they’re a little more frequent! From the embarrassing to the painful and a little bit of the in-between, check out what the Riverdale gang considers the worst day ever!

An American writer of heroic fantasy books, Jack Kelsey, disappeared from his New England home. Some time before, also his wife Linda had misteriously vanished; in an interview released to Timothy O’Sullivan, Kelsey said that he had really met his own characters, and had made love with his beautiful warrior girl, Rhaleya. After finding the name of Xeethra, his lost princess, in one of Kelsey’s dime novels, Kurjak go in search of the writer. Instead of ending up in the Twilight World, though, Kurjak, having lost his memory, will find himself in a wild land where the Hordes of Chaos led by Prince Alastor fight against the humans. And Kurjak, the only man in a fellowship of hired warrior women, will go into service of the Prince of Hell!
name: Il Segno di Alastor

description: While Kurjak, together with the Sisterhood of the beautiful mercenaries, finds out that he has to join the Army of Chaos, led by the ruthless Prince Alastor, Harlan sails the seas on a pirate ship, to steal the treasures of a God on the gloomy Torturers’ Island. Exiled in that faraway world, both of them lost their memories... and Fate threatens to put one against the other!
name: Il Trono del Dio Oscuro

description: This cover was printed with a wrong price (L. 1.000). A sticker was used to fix the cover to the right price (L. 2.000)!
name: Una Bernarda da Re
